ext 10-12 minutes it continued to tell me I had an active character.  Finally, it let me begin loading the game once again.  I selected Hodur and hit the Enter World button.  After about 15 seconds, my connectivity light went orange again (orange = bad, green = good), and stayed that way for at least 20 minutes, so I went to bed.  I was still disconnected from the internet this morning when I went to work. <br><br>Does anyone have any advice or help they can give me?  Re-installing EQ doesn't help.  I have updated drivers.  Insight@home (run by Cox Cable) is my internet provider.  Since the patch that added focus items, I have been unable to camp.  The game locks up around 90% of the time.  I just have to restart the game and reload everything, which is time consuming.  <br><br>So anyway, I hope to be on tonight, but who knows.  It seems the gods of the internet and of computers are conspiring against me.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#767676><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ukaminite.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaminite</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#B30000>(6/12/02 7:38:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=242.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why I hate computers.</span><hr size=1> When i was having sooo much trouble in the grey.. i turned off all the new models cept for the ones for the people i group with all the time, wef bf bm, and i was much better about crashing after that...  perhaps your cpu or video card are getting too hot? Anyways i wish you the best of luck and may the computer/net gods quit picking on you <p><center><font color="black" font="Comic Sans MS"><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=186435><img src="http://www.geocities.com/character8in/